{"type":"message","id":"8f592f16","parentId":"390735a0","timestamp":"2026-04-14T13:41:37.105Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"There it is! The workspace is set to `/home/ai/.openclaw/workspace`. So the session-summary hook writes to `/home/ai/.openclaw/workspace/memory/`.\n\nBut my agent's workspace is `/home/ai/.openclaw/workspace/main/`. The memory files I see in my context are at `/home/ai/.openclaw/workspace/main/memory/`.\n\nSo there are TWO memory directories:\n1. `/home/ai/.openclaw/workspace/memory/` - where session-summary hook writes\n2. `/home/ai/.openclaw/workspace/main/memory/` - my agent's memory directory (from the workspace context)\n\n\nAnd when I search for session-summary files, I found one at `/home/ai/.openclaw/workspace/memory/2026-04-13-session-summary.md`, but the bootstrap hook looks for `*-session-summary.md` files and my session has been creating files like `2026-04-14-session-hook-debug.md` instead. The naming convention seems inconsistent with what the bootstrap hook is expecting.\n\nThe actual file being written is `2026-04-14-无会话内容.md` from the session-summary hook, but bootstrap is searching for `*-session-summary.md` — there's a clear mismatch. I should check whether this is a deliberate naming scheme or a bug in how the hooks are generating filenames.","thinkingSignature":"a7587498c0deab3238b659a5fdf5ffb63b044ba1f0aab9444b28b0f012a51d5b"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_y0rs06t8uuf9_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"grep -n \"session-summary\\|slug\" /home/ai/.openclaw/hooks/handler.js | head -20"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":14231,"output":332,"cacheRead":19750,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":34313,"cost":{"input":0.0042693,"output":0.0003984,"cacheRead":0.0011849999999999999,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.005852700000000001}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776174088452,"responseId":"062d7708643cabc18f6c3dc9500a1902"}}
