{"type":"message","id":"d3c9cb73","parentId":"36ee3fba","timestamp":"2026-04-14T13:41:50.346Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Found the bug! The bootstrap hook's `getLatestSessionSummary()` function looks for files ending with `-session-summary.md`:\n\n```javascript\nconst summaryFiles = files.filter(f => f.endsWith('-session-summary.md'));\n```\n\nBut the session-summary hook writes files named `${date}-${slug}.md` like `2026-04-14-无会话内容.md`.\n\nThese two are completely incompatible naming conventions!\n\nThe session-summary hook SHOULD write files with a name containing \"session-summary\" so the bootstrap hook can find them. But the current code writes `YYYY-MM-DD-{slug}.md` where slug is derived from the summary content.\n \nNow I'm realizing the session-summary hook is a shared resource across all agents using that hook name, so changing the naming convention could affect other parts of the system. I need to figure out what slug is actually being generated for my sessions to understand whether the naming mismatch is the root cause or if there's something else going on with how these files are being discovered.","thinkingSignature":"95066b9cfdee34e6ffa41363afc09f2d9c697fa6743fe6e572f3a547d6ab17ff"},{"type":"text","text":"找到断点了。\n\n**问题确认**：session-summary hook 写的是 `2026-04-14-无会话内容.md` 这种格式，但 bootstrap hook 在找 `*-session-summary.md` 文件——**文件名格式完全对不上**。\n\n| 环节 | 文件名格式 | 状态 |\n|------|-----------|------|\n| session-summary hook 写文件 | `YYYY-MM-DD-{slug}.md` | ✅ 写了 |\n| bootstrap hook 找文件 | `*-session-summary.md` | ❌ 找不到 |\n\n这就是为什么 bootstrap 注入了寂寞——根本没文件可读。\n\n**修复方案**：session-summary hook 写文件时，slug 应该包含 \"session-summary\" 字符串，这样 bootstrap 才能匹配上。要我现在修吗？"}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":14655,"output":356,"cacheRead":19750,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":34761,"cost":{"input":0.0043965,"output":0.0004272,"cacheRead":0.0011849999999999999,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.0060087