{"type":"message","id":"c2e991d2","parentId":"e1c64e3b","timestamp":"2026-04-14T13:42:40.462Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user wants me to fix the session-summary hook's filename format so it matches what bootstrap hook is looking for. Let me look at the slug generation code.","thinkingSignature":"1ee3552fea122b425b3d661345688b5b68b1ce034c6fccdb2ef63be0671f1231"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_oy7pkco4n4ss_1","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"/home/ai/.openclaw/hooks/session-summary/handler.js","offset":570,"limit":40}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":54,"output":92,"cacheRead":19750,"cacheWrite":12584,"totalTokens":32480,"cost":{"input":0.0000162,"output":0.0001104,"cacheRead":0.0011849999999999999,"cacheWrite":0.004719,"total":0.0060306}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776174152808,"responseId":"062d7748fbfb59e06d58ae686fd09cff"}}
{"type":"message","id":"67efbdd0","parentId":"c2e991d2","timestamp":"2026-04-14T13:42:40.531Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_oy7pkco4n4ss_1","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"\n/**\n * @param {string} summary\n * @param {string} time\n * @returns {string}\n */\nfunction slugFromSummary(summary, time) {\n  const match = summary.match(/^## 主题$\\s*([^\\n]+)/m);\n  if (!match) return time.replace(/:/g, \"\");\n\n  return match[1]\n    .toLowerCase()\n    .replace(/[^a-z0-9\\u4e00-\\u9fff]+/g, \"-\")\n    .replace(/^-+|-+$/g, \"\")\n    .slice(0, 40) || time.replace(/:/g, \"\");\n}\n\n// ─── Session Summary Pruning ────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n\nconst MAX_SUMMARY_AGE_DAYS = 30;\n\n/**\n * 删除 30 天前的旧 session-summary 文件，防止累积。\n * @returns {Promise<void>}\n */\nasync function pruneOldSummaries() {\n  try {\n    const files = await fs.promises.readdir(MEMORY_DIR);\n    const now = Date.now();\n    const maxAge = MAX_SUMMARY_AGE_DAYS * 24 * 60 * 60 * 1000;\n    let pruned = 0;\n\n    for (const file of files) {\n      if (!file.endsWith('-session-summary.md')) continue;\n      const filePath = path.join(MEMORY_DIR, file);\n      const stat = await fs.promises.stat(filePath);\n      if (now - stat.mtimeMs > maxAge) {\n        await fs.promises.unlink(filePath);\n        pruned++;\n      }\n\n[71 more lines in file. Use offset=610 to continue.]"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1776174160521}}
{"type":"message","id":"d7916c02","parentId":"67efbdd0","timestamp":"2026-04-14T13:42:47.357Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I see the issue clearly:\n\n1. `slugFromSummary()` generates a slug from the summary content - if no `## 主题` is found, it just uses the time.\n2. The file is written as `${date}-${slug}.md` (e.g., `2026-04-14-无会话内容.md`)\n3. But the bootstrap hook looks for files ending with `-session-summary.md`\n4. The `pruneOldSummaries()` function also looks for `-session-summary.md` files\n\nThe fix is simple: force the filename to always include \"session-summary\" as part of the slug. The simplest approach: always prefix the slug with \"session-summary-\".","thinkingSignature":"05640493f06b854d23cea303b870973fdfe13d29a7ef786db9452d5a7626a208"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_6y47nifj8ukj_1","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"/home/ai/.openclaw/hooks/session-summary/handler.js","offset":545,"limit":30}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":13086,"output":202,"cacheRead":19750,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":33038,"cost":{"input":0.0039258,"output":0.00024239999999999998,"cacheRead":0.0011849999999999999,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.005353200000000001}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776174160532,"responseId":"062d77509068a6db814fdfc28bd36801"}}
{"type":"message","id":"9f6ab76a","parentId":"d7916c02","timestamp":"2026-04-14T13:42:47.429Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_6y47nifj8ukj_1","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":" * @param {string} summary\n * @param {string} date\n * @param {string} time\n * @param {string} sessionKey\n * @returns {Promise<void>}\n */\nasync function writeSummaryFile(summary, date, time, sessionKey) {\n  const slug = slugFromSummary(summary, time);\n  const filename = `${date}-${slug}.md`;\n  const filePath = path.join(MEMORY_DIR, filename);\n\n  await fs.promises.mkdir(MEMORY_DIR, { recursive: true });\n\n  const fullContent = [\n    `# Session: ${date} ${time}`,\n    \"\",\n    \"<!-- summary-only -->\",\n    summary,\n    \"\",\n    `<!-- source: ${sessionKey} -->`,\n  ].join(\"\\n\");\n\n  await fs.promises.writeFile(filePath, fullContent, \"utf-8\");\n  console.log(`[session-summary] Written: ${filename}`);\n}\n\n/**\n * @param {string} summary\n * @param {string} time\n * @returns {string}\n\n[106 more lines in file. Use offset=575 to continue.]"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1776174167415}}
{"type":"message","id":"9c8ca7f2","parentId":"9f6ab76a","timestamp":"2026-04-14T13:42:52.574Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The fix is straightforward: change the filename pattern to always include \"session-summary\" in the filename. Let me modify line 553:\n\nChange:\n```javascript\nconst filename = `${date}-${slug}.md`;\n```\nTo:\n```javascript\nconst filename = `${date}-session-summary-${slug}.md`;\n```\n\nThis ensures the file always ends with `-session-summary.md` which is what the bootstrap hook and pruneOldSummaries() are looking for.","thinkingSignature":"95c118447203904a90b5279aea97ed0bd38e00527e1585ec0cbb2d97d4722a24"},{"type":"text","text":"改动只有一行——在文件名里强制塞入 `session-summary`。\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_hn2yyxulafz4_1","name":"edit","arguments":{"path":"/home/ai/.openclaw/hooks/session-summary/handler.js","edits":[{"oldText":"  const slug = slugFromSummary(summary, time);\n  const filename = `${date}-${slug}.md`;","newText":"  const slug = slugFromSummary(summary, time);\n  const filename = `${date}-session-summary-${slug}.md`;"}]}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":13532,"output":219,"cacheRead":19750,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":33501,"cost":{"input":0.0040596,"output":0.0002628,"cacheRead":0.0011849999999999999,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.005507399999999999}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776174167429,"responseId":"062d7756c2bff2f5f1efe125c4531ef0"}}
