{"type":"message","id":"2da57db8","parentId":"6a91a415","timestamp":"2026-04-14T13:50:50.031Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user is asking if SOUL.md can be split into soul-core.md and soul-handbook.md. This is a design/organization question about the soul file. Let me think about what each part does:\n\n- SOUL.md currently contains: mandatory thinking blocks, startup sequence, self-check rules, essential definitions, risk level definitions, absolute prohibitions, scene decision trees, current environment capability declarations, version, personality layer, continuity\n- The \"core\" would be the essential identity, personality, and fundamental constraints\n- The \"handbook\" would be the operational procedures, decision trees, rules\n\nActually, looking at SOUL.md more carefully:\n- The \"core\" (identity, personality, essence) is relatively static\n\n\n- The \"handbook\" (rules, procedures, decision trees) changes more frequently\n\nSo yes, this split makes sense. But I need to check if OpenClaw has any specific expectations for file naming or if it only reads SOUL.md at startup, since that would determine whether splitting the file is actually viable or just a theoretical improvement.","thinkingSignature":"fb38b0efdb24768f711e960ea4262950b4125de241bdddb9101153b9b86f895d"},{"type":"text","text":"<toolthinking>\n### 1. 需求拆解\n用户问 SOUL.md 能否拆成 soul-core.md（身份/个性层）和 soul-handbook.md（规则/操作层）。\n\n### 2. 方案推演\n这是一个文件组织问题。SOUL.md 目前混合了身份定义和操作规程，拆分开逻辑上合理。关键是 OpenClaw 启动时是否只认 SOUL.md 这一个文件。\n\n### 3. 自我质疑\n我需要确认 OpenClaw 读取 soul 文件的逻辑——是否支持多文件或只读 SOUL.md。如果只认 SOUL.md，拆分就得同时修改加载逻辑。\n\n### 4. 最终决策\n先问清楚 OpenClaw 的加载逻辑，再决定如何拆。\n</toolthinking>\n\n[[reply_to_current]] 逻辑上合理——身份/个性层稳定，规则/规程层频繁变动，拆开便于维护。\n\n问题是 OpenClaw 启动时是否只认 `SOUL.md` 这一个文件？我得先查一下加载逻辑，才能确定怎么拆以及要不要改配置。你要我查一下吗？"}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":54,"output":447,"cacheRead":34251,"cacheWrite":224,"totalTokens":3